  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7039 sitting between the negative gamma pocket at 7015 (-1513.8M) and the massive positive gamma wall at 7050 (+12175.3M), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push toward 7050 while providing buying support on dips toward 7015-7000. The PIN regime with 117B in total GEX creates a strong mean-reversion environment, with the recent wall break and GEX surge events suggesting dealers just absorbed significant flow and are now heavily positioned to dampen volatility. Key battle zone is 7015-7050, with 7000 acting as the major support backstop and 7050-7100 forming a formidable resistance ceiling where dealer selling pressure intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect tight range-bound trading between 7015-7050 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
